[[Image:Tenue Abron 01.JPG|thumb|Abron musician]]
The '''Abron''' or '''Bono''' are an [[Akan people]] of [[West Africa]].<ref>Other name variations: '''Brong''', '''Boron''', '''Borong''', or '''Bron'''</ref> They speak the [[Abron language]].

In the late sixteenth century, the Abron founded the [[Gyaaman]] kingdom as extension of [[Bono state]] in what is now [[Ghana]] and [[Côte d'Ivoire]].

