|Ship boats=*2 × [[rigid-hulled inflatable boat]]s *1 × Atlas Elektronik Seafox [[Remotely operated underwater vehicle|remote controlled submersible]] for mine identification and disposal |Ship capacity= |Ship troops= |Ship complement=4 officers, 15 non-commissioned officers, 17 sailors |Ship sensors=*1 Thales Underwater Systems TSM 2022 Mk III Hull Mounted Sonar *1 SAAB Bofors Double Eagle Mk III Self Propelled Variable Depth Sonar *1 Consilium Selesmar Type T-250/10CM003 Radar |Ship EW= |Ship armament=3 × [[Fabrique Nationale de Herstal|FN]] [[M2 Browning machine gun|.50 caliber (12.7 mm)]] [[machine gun]]s |Ship armour= |Ship aircraft= |Ship aircraft facilities= |Ship notes= }} |} '''''Bellis'' (M916)''' is a {{sclass2-|Tripartite|minehunter}} of the [[Belgian Naval Component]], launched on 14 February 1986 at the Mercantile-Belyard shipyard in [[Rupelmonde]] and [[Ship naming and launching|christened]] by Ellen Goffinet-Rosman, the wife of the then Mayor of Arlon, on 18 September 1986. The patronage of ''Bellis'' was accepted by the city of [[Arlon]]. It was the second of the Belgian Tripartite-class minehunters.<ref name="mil.be">{{cite web |url=http://www.mil.be/navycomp/units/index.asp?LAN=fr&FILE=unittext&ID=661&MENU=196&PAGE=1 |title=Composante Marine Unités M916 Bellis - Mijnenjager (Tripartite) Généralités |publisher=www.mil.be |accessdate=2009-11-20 |language=fr}}</ref>
Commissioned on 13 August 1986, the ship participated the rescue of the survivors of ferry {{MS|Herald of Free Enterprise}} in March 1987 which had capsized outside the [[port of Zeebrugge]].<ref name="mil.be"/>
''Bellis'' was attached to [[NATO]]'s [[Standing NRF Mine Countermeasures Group 1|Mine Countermeasure Force (North)]] (MCMFORNORTH) in 1987, 1990, 1996, 1998, 1999, 2002 and 2004, and to [[Standing NRF Mine Countermeasures Group 2|Mine Countermeasures Force (South)]] (MCMFORSOUTH) in 1992, 1995, 1997, 1999, and 2003.<ref name="mil.be"/>
It is currently commanded by [[Ship-of-the-Line Lieutenant|Lieutenant]] First Class [http://www.mil.be/navycomp/cv/index.asp?LAN=fr&ID=69&FILE=cvtext&MENU=1&PAGE=1 Emmanuel Verhaege].<ref name="mil.be"/>
