The '''Finnish Standards Association''' ('''SFS''', {{lang-fi|Suomen Standardisoimisliitto SFS ry}}, {{lang-sv|Finlands Standardiseringsförbund}}) is the central [[standards organization]] in [[Finland]]. It is a member organization of the [[International Organization for Standardization|ISO]] and [[European Committee for Standardization|CEN]], representing Finland in these organizations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sfs.fi/en/sfs_in_brief|title=SFS in brief|accessdate=17 June 2018}}</ref> SFS is responsible for both international and national standards, with the former being translated from ISO standards. The organization acts as a central organization for 13 different national standards writing bodies, such as [[SESKO]] and [[FICORA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.iso.org/member/1734.html|title=SFS - Finnish Standards Association SFS|publisher=[[International Organization for Standardization|ISO]]|accessdate=17 June 2018}}</ref>
