'''Shahid Salahuddin Cantonment''' is a cantonment located in [[Ghatail Upazila]], [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka, Delhi preparing for PM's visit to India in Dec|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/dhaka-delhi-preparing-pms-visit-india-dec-1309327|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en|date=4 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Cautious, yet Nikhil could not survive|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/frontpage/cautious-yet-he-could-not-survive-1217824|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en|date=3 May 2016}}</ref> Ghatail Area Commander is Major General [[Sajjadul Haque (officer)|Sajjadul Haque]].<ref name="dxs">{{cite web|title=Ghatail Area Commander and General Officer Commanding of 19 Infantry Division Maj Gen Sajjadul Haque, afwc, psc was present as Chief Guest and distributed prizes among the winners. of Army Archery competition at Shaheed Salahuddin Cantonment at Ghatail, Tangail on Thurday.|url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/110002/ghatail-area-commander-and-general-officer-commanding-of-19-infantry-division--maj-gen-sajjadul-haque-afwc-psc-was-present-as-chief-guest-and-distributed-prizes-among-the-winners-of-army-archery-competition-at-shaheed-salahuddin-cantonment--at-ghatail-tangail-on-thurday.html|website=The New Nation|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>
==History== On 09 Novembor 2009 Chief Of General Staff (CGS) of Bangladesh Army witnessed first firing of recoilless rifle of Ghatail Field Firing Range .On 12 February 2014, two army soldiers and three soldiers of Border Guard Bangladesh died in a shell explosion at the firing range. On 28 August 2014, three children were injured at the range after a shell they were playing with exploded.<ref>{{cite web|title=3 children hurt in firing range shell blast|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/3-children-hurt-in-firing-range-shell-blast-47788|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en|date=28 October 2014}}</ref> Bangladesh and [[India]] held joint military exercise in [[counter terrorism]] and disaster management, at the cantonment from 5 November 2016 to 18 November 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh, India joint military exercise from Nov 5|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/country/bangladesh-india-joint-military-exercise-nov-5-1308898|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en|date=3 November 2016}}</ref> Bangladesh Army Archery Competition in 2016 was held at the cantonment.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladesh Army Archery ends|url=http://www.daily-sun.com/post/173546/Bangladesh-Army-Archery-ends|website=daily-sun.com|publisher=The Daily Sun|accessdate=3 April 2017|language=en}}</ref>
